05 — Current Work
AI SECURITY PIPELINE

Currently architecting an AI-powered CVE/CWE intelligence pipeline — a multi-phase product that transforms raw vulnerability data into actionable security intelligence using state-of-the-art LLM technology.

The system ingests CVE data from Debian, CVE MITRE, RHEL/HYDRA, and Canonical APIs, builds vector-indexed knowledge bases, and applies fine-tuned LLMs to deliver automated attack path classification, vulnerability prioritisation, and security hotspot detection.

watsonx.ai Granite
LoRA Fine-Tuning (7–8B)
pgvector / PostgreSQL
MCP Server
RAG Pipeline
CVE MITRE API
Python / Go
RHEL HYDRA
📥
Phase 1
CVE Aggregation & Knowledge Base
Multi-source CVE ingestion (Debian, MITRE, RHEL, Canonical) → Vector embedding → pgvector knowledge base → CVE-to-CWE mapping via quantized LoRA fine-tuning (7–8B models).
🗂️
Phase 2
Architecture Indexing & Attack Classification
Architecture component indexing → Vulnerability category mapping → AI-driven attack path classification → Security hotspot detection using watsonx.ai Granite.
🖼️
Phase 3
Image-Format Ingestion Support
Extend pipeline to support container image-format vulnerability scanning → automated prioritisation → integrated remediation recommendations via MCP Server.
